SE Coding Proficiency Test (2 Hours)

Assume you have a pipe delimited file with column headers, 3 columns, and 1,000,451 rows.

  • ID Unique Character

  • Region Character with 5 levels (NW, SW, C, NE, SE)

  • Amount Numeric in Dollars

 

Create an R function called calcVar_YourName to calculate the exact variance of Amount for all the data, given the constraint that you cant fit more than 100k rows into memory at a time.  This should return a single value, and should minimally takes the pipe delimited file as an argument, i.e. calcVar_yourName <- function(file){}. Other arguments are acceptable if it helps build the functionality.
